<sect1 xml:id="sec.depl.poc.intro">
  <title>About This Document</title>
  <para>
   This document is intended to be a starting point for a &cloud;
   implementation. You can use it as a guide that can help you prepare
   deployment and as a worksheet for discussing &cloud; configuration for your
   environment.
  </para>
  <para>
    The topics below are covered in greater detail in the &cloud; deployment
    guide. Refer to this guide for clarifications and term
    definitions. References throughout the document point to the relevant
    sections in the deployment guide.
  </para>
</sect1>
<sect1 xml:id="sec.depl.poc.prelim">
  <title>Planning Your Cloud: Preliminary Considerations</title>
  <para>
    <remark>dpopov 2016-11-11: To better understand how to optimize your cloud, consider the following points:</remark>Some questions to answer to help you understand how you want to optimize your cloud.
  </para>
  <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
    <listitem>
      <para>
	<remark>dpopov 2016-11-11: What problem a private
	Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) cloud is going to solve for you?</remark>
	What problem are you trying to solve by implementing a private
	Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) cloud?
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><remark>dpopov 2016-11-11: Who are your users, and what do they expect from your cloud?</remark>Who are the users for your cloud? What do they want out of your cloud?
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	<remark>dpopov 2016-11-11: What are your business and technical requirements (service level agreements, regulatory compliance, etc.)?</remark>What are your business and technical requirements? Example requirements are Service Level 
	Agreements (SLAâ€™s), regulatory compliance, etc.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><remark>dpopov 2016-11-11: What are the project's constraints (budget, deadline, manpower, etc.)?</remark>What are the constraints for this project? Example constraints are budget, deadline, manpower.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	What additional resources are required for a successful deployment?
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</sect1>
<sect1 xml:id="sec.depl.poc.guide">
    <title><remark>dpopov 2016-11-11: Proof-of-Concept Deployment Guidelines</remark>
    POC Guide</title>
    <para><remark>dpopov 2016-11-11: For a proof-of-concept (POC) deployment, consider taking the following steps:</remark>If you are using this guide to deploy a proof-of-concept (POC), here are some additional steps to consider taking
    </para>
    <procedure><title>Before the POC deployment</title>
    <step>
      <para>
	Schedule a meeting to go through the following topics:
      </para>
      <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
      <para>
	Networking: Public network/nova floating range. Is Bastion configuration required? VLANs (Admin network cannot be tagged)
      </para>
      </listitem>
          <listitem>
	    <para>
	      Source for media and SMT repositories (ex. USB drive brought by SE)
	    </para>
	  </listitem>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
	      Backup/restore plan for the admin server if the installation must be repeated
	     </para>
	  </listitem>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
	      Confirm that the BIOS, FC cards, Network and BMC's are all updated to the latest firmware from the manufacturer.
	     </para>
	    </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
	Build a SLE11 SP3 JeOS image using &susestudio; with <systemitem class="resource">supportutils</systemitem> package and setup network configuration with &yast; at firstboot
      </para>
    </step>
    </procedure>

    <procedure><title>First day of the POC deployment</title>
    <step>
      <para>
	Bring SLE11 SP3 JeOS image
      </para>
      <itemizedlist>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Collect a supportconfig from all systems that will be part of the cloud infrastructure
	   </para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Use the supportconfigs to review interface map/network conduit/network info in network.json (See <xref linkend="app.deploy.network_json"/>)
	   </para>
	  </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </step>
    </procedure>
</sect1>
